# NSUserActivity.TypedPayloadError.encodingError

**Case**

An encoding error that indicates that the content failed to encode into a valid dictionary.

## Declaration

```swift
case encodingError
```

## Discussion

The [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSUserActivity/setTypedPayload(_:)] method throws this error.

## Typed payload errors

- **NSUserActivity.TypedPayloadError.invalidContent**: A decoding error that indicates that the user info dictionary is empty or invalid.
